.SH NAME
WritableStreamDefaultController \- WritableStreamDefaultController
.SH SYNOPSIS
This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]WritableStreamDefaultController\f[B]\f[R] interface of
the Streams API represents a controller allowing control of a
\f[CR]WritableStream\f[R]\[cq]s state.
When constructing a \f[CR]WritableStream\f[R], the underlying sink is
given a corresponding \f[CR]WritableStreamDefaultController\f[R]
instance to manipulate.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
None.
\f[CR]WritableStreamDefaultController\f[R] instances are created
automatically during \f[CR]WritableStream\f[R] construction.
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
.TP
\f[B]WritableStreamDefaultController.signal\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns the \f[CR]AbortSignal\f[R] associated with the controller.
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
.TP
\f[B]WritableStreamDefaultController.error()\f[R]
Causes any future interactions with the associated stream to error.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] writableStream = \f[B]new\f[R] WritableStream({
  start(controller) {
    \f[I]// do stuff with controller\f[R]

    \f[I]// error stream if necessary\f[R]
    controller.error(\[dq]My stream is broken\[dq]);
  },
  write(chunk, controller) {
    \f[I]// ...\f[R]
  },
  close(controller) {
    \f[I]// ...\f[R]
  },
  abort(err) {
    \f[I]// ...\f[R]
  },
});
